  "time_ut": 1657086689,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0bb4\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The tea industry is in decline",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Rozan Rajadurai, Media Spokesperson of Plantation Owners Association said that due to non-availability of fuel required for tea production, the current economic crisis has caused more suffering.",
        "A large amount of petrol and diesel is required daily to transport the plucked pulp from the tea plantations to the tea factories and for the production of tea powder.",
        "Also, in the midst of the current blackout, there is a huge demand for fuel for tea production, and problems have arisen in transporting tea powder for auction sale.",
        "In addition, 10 lakh people are directly and indirectly connected with the tea industry. If the tea industry collapses, Sri Lanka's main source of foreign exchange will be disrupted and the livelihoods of 10 lakh people will be affected.",
        "On the question of the countries that import tea from Sri Lanka, if tea is not exported, the countries concerned will start importing tea from countries like India and Kenya.",
        "Therefore, he has requested that the Sri Lankan Fuel Cooperative should take steps to distribute the required fuel to the plantation companies, and pointed out that there are warehouse facilities for storing fuel in the plantations."
      ],
